"{\"uid\": \"independent.co.uk-life-style-tom-cruise-stunt-paris-olympics-b2612848.html\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"Notifications can be managed in browser preferences.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 52, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Please refresh the page or navigate to another page on the site to be automatically logged inPlease refresh your browser to be logged in  Swipe for next article  Olympics chair Wasserman was told: 'It's never happening'  Removed from bookmarks  I would like to be emailed about offers, events and updates from The Independent.\", \"from\": 54, \"to\": 380, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 231, \"end\": 240, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Wasserman_Media_Group\", \"score\": 0.9999969474034722, \"rank\": 3.0351158524206157e-06, \"text\": \"Wasserman\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Wasserman_Media_Group\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Wasserman_Media_Group\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Read ourPrivacy notice  Tom Cruiseagreed to do hisdivisive stunt at the competition's 2024 closing ceremonyin Paris - but only on two conditions.\", \"from\": 381, \"to\": 526, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 491, \"end\": 496, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999995757207, \"rank\": 4.243305535362379e-10, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Marking the handover fromParistoLos Angeles- where the 2028 games will be hosted - the 62-year-oldMission: Impossibleactordramatically abseiled off the Stade de France roof, landed in a crowd of fans before hopping on a motorbike and riding out of thestadium while holding the Olympic flag.\", \"from\": 528, \"to\": 818, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 680, \"end\": 695, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stade_de_France\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Stade de France\", \"types\": [\"Q41176\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stade_de_France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stade_de_France\"}, {\"begin\": 680, \"end\": 695, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stade_de_France\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Stade de France\", \"types\": [\"Q41176\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stade_de_France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stade_de_France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"TheTop Gunactor, who isnotorious for performing all of his own stunts,was then shown on a pre-recorded film travelling through Paris and driving the bike on to a plane.\", \"from\": 820, \"to\": 988, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 947, \"end\": 952, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999995757207, \"rank\": 4.243305535362379e-10, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He then parachuted down to the crowd and landed at the Hollywood sign in LA.\", \"from\": 989, \"to\": 1065, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1044, \"end\": 1058, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hollywood_Sign\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Hollywood sign\", \"types\": [\"Q41176\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hollywood_Sign\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hollywood_Sign\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Casey Wasserman, president and chairman of the LA28 games, explained the story behind the stunt at a CNBC x Boardroom: Game Plan Panel in Santa Monica, according toThe Hollywood Reporter.\", \"from\": 1067, \"to\": 1254, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1067, \"end\": 1082, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Casey_Wasserman\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Casey Wasserman\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Casey_Wasserman\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Casey_Wasserman\"}, {\"begin\": 1168, \"end\": 1172, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/CNBC\", \"score\": 0.9999999982751433, \"rank\": 1.5416229903155363e-09, \"text\": \"CNBC\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q15265344\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/CNBC\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/CNBC\"}, {\"begin\": 1205, \"end\": 1217, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Santa_Monica_Boulevard\", \"score\": 0.9973962231228262, \"rank\": 0.0026105702255359462, \"text\": \"Santa Monica\", \"types\": [\"Q34442\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Santa_Monica_Boulevard\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Santa_Monica_Boulevard\"}, {\"begin\": 1235, \"end\": 1244, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cinema_of_the_United_States\", \"score\": 0.9999999992696758, \"rank\": 7.303810824312435e-10, \"text\": \"Hollywood\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cinema_of_the_United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cinema_of_the_United_States\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"The best part of the story is we pitched on a Zoom, and the original idea was a person in the stadium as a stunt double,\\\" he said.\", \"from\": 1256, \"to\": 1387, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"We are like, 'Well, there is no way we are getting this.\", \"from\": 1389, \"to\": 1446, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"We are going to get four hours of filming time.\", \"from\": 1447, \"to\": 1494, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"We will do the thing [in LA} with the Hollywood sign, he will hand the thing off and he's done.\", \"from\": 1495, \"to\": 1590, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1533, \"end\": 1547, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hollywood_Sign\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Hollywood sign\", \"types\": [\"Q41176\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hollywood_Sign\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hollywood_Sign\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Maybe we will get the other stuff and the rest will be just a stunt double.'\", \"from\": 1592, \"to\": 1669, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"About five minutes into the presentation [Tom Cruise] goes, 'I am in.\", \"from\": 1670, \"to\": 1739, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1712, \"end\": 1722, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tom_Cruise\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Tom Cruise\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tom_Cruise\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tom_Cruise\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But I am only doing it if I get to do everything.'\\\"\", \"from\": 1740, \"to\": 1791, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"In addition to the first condition of him performing his own stunts, Cruise also insisted on doing the performance for free.\", \"from\": 1793, \"to\": 1917, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"TV producer Ben Winston was pivotal in organising the event and recommended either Cruise's involvement or a \\\"David Blaine kind of thing\\\" with Olympic rings appearing out of the ocean.\", \"from\": 1919, \"to\": 2103, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1931, \"end\": 1942, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ben_Winston\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Ben Winston\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ben_Winston\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ben_Winston\"}, {\"begin\": 2029, \"end\": 2041, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/David_Blaine\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"David Blaine\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/David_Blaine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/David_Blaine\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Wasserman explained that Winston rang him after the Zoom call.\", \"from\": 2105, \"to\": 2167, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2105, \"end\": 2114, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Wasserman_Media_Group\", \"score\": 0.9999969474034722, \"rank\": 3.0351158524206157e-06, \"text\": \"Wasserman\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Wasserman_Media_Group\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Wasserman_Media_Group\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"He says, 'Do not get too excited.\", \"from\": 2169, \"to\": 2203, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"He loves doing this stuff, but when his team realises how many shooting days it's going to be and rehearsals, this is never happening.\", \"from\": 2204, \"to\": 2338, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I am telling you I got it, but it's never happening.'\", \"from\": 2340, \"to\": 2394, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Sure enough, every step of the way, he got more involved and more engaged.\\\"\", \"from\": 2395, \"to\": 2470, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Cruise did end up performing the stunt, however, he appeared to have set his own bar too high as some fans thought it was predictable.\", \"from\": 2472, \"to\": 2606, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Happy Olympics Closing Ceremony or as it's better known Tom Cruise Is Gonna Do a Crazy Stunt Day,\\\" wrote one viewer on X/Twitter.\", \"from\": 2608, \"to\": 2738, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2665, \"end\": 2675, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tom_Cruise\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Tom Cruise\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tom_Cruise\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tom_Cruise\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Another called the stunt \\\"totally unsurprising,\\\" adding: \\\"I can imagine Tom Cruise doing [something] like this on a casual Tuesday\\\".\", \"from\": 2740, \"to\": 2872, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2812, \"end\": 2822, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tom_Cruise\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Tom Cruise\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tom_Cruise\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tom_Cruise\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Join thought-provoking conversations, follow other Independent readers and see their replies  Please refresh the page or navigate to another page on the site to be automatically logged inPlease refresh your browser to be logged in\", \"from\": 2874, \"to\": 3104, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2925, \"end\": 2936, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Independent\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 7.428359770532954e-15, \"text\": \"Independent\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\", \"Q234460\", \"Q11032\", \"Q1092563\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Independent\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Independent\"}]}]}"